observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the LCE require the: 

(a) Municipal Disaster and Risk Reduction Management Officer  to (i) submit the monthly Report on the Sources and Utilization of LDRRMF as prescribed in COA Circular No. 2012-002 dated  September 12, 2012 to the Office of the Auditor for timely review and evaluation of the same to attain transparency and accountability in the use of LDRRMF; 

(ii) prepare and submit the Inventory of Disaster Equipment as of year-end; and 

(iii) maintain an organized inventory-keeping of DRRM equipment, supplies and materials for the efficient management of the same; 

(b) Municipal Treasurer to issue acknowledgement receipt in the prescribed form for all donations in-kind received containing the complete details of the goods donated; and 

(c) Municipal Accountant to prepare the necessary adjusting entries to correctly classify the procurement of welfare goods and the expenses incurred in the implementation of programs, projects and activities to the appropriate accounts.

We recommended that the LCE 

(a) instruct the Municipal Development Council to  adhere strictly  to the guidelines on  project identification and inclusion in the AIP of the programs, projects and activities of the 20% DF pursuant to JMC No. 2017-1 dated February 22, 2017; 

(b) require the  Bids and Awards Committee and the Municipal Engineer to ensure that the  awarded infrastructure projects conform with the documentary requirements provided by the 2016 IRR of R.A. No. 9184 and  Sec 4.1 of GPPB Circular No. 2020-1; 

(c) require the Municipal Accountant to ensure the completeness of the documentary requirements for infrastructure projects prior to payment COA Circular No. 2012-001 dated June 14, 2012.

